04/07/2006
VARNA, Bulgaria -- A four-day military drill titled "Breeze 2006" kicked off near Varna in the Bulgarian Black Sea on Monday (3 July).
It includes six nations -- Bulgaria, France, Greece, Italy, Turkey and the United States -- and is aimed at improving co-ordination and capacities for humanitarian assistance in cases of natural disasters and catastrophes.
Later this month, another military exercise involving Bulgarian, Romanian and American soldiers will take place at Bulgaria's Novo Selo base and Romania's Capu Midia.
(Sega - 04/07/06;
BNR, Bulgarian Government Web site - 03/07/06)
